	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2014-07-16T04:32:50">Microsoft Corporation is engaged in developing, licensing and supporting a range of software products and services. The Company also designs and sells hardware, and delivers online advertising to the customers. The Company operates in five segments: Windows &amp; Windows Live Division (Windows Division), Server and Tools, Online Services Division (OSD), Microsoft Business Division (MBD), and Entertainment and Devices Division (EDD). The Companys products include operating systems for personal computers (PCs), servers, phones, and other intelligent devices; server applications for distributed computing environments; productivity applications; business solution applications; desktop and server management tools; software development tools; video games, and online advertising. Effective July 11, 2014, Microsoft Corp acquired InMage Systems Inc.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2014-09-22T14:37:35">BRIEF: For the fiscal year ended 30 June 2014, Microsoft Corporation revenues increased 12% to $86.83B. Net income increased 1% to $22.07B. Revenues reflect DeVices and Consumer-Hardware segment increase of 49% to $9.63B, Commercial- Licensing segment increase of 6% to $42.03B, Devices and Consumer-Phone Hardware segment increase from $0K to $1.99B, Outside the United States/Other Countries. segment increase of 19% to $43.36B.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
